race.comment: Competitive. SACRED FORT (5) didn't handle the heavy surface at Warrnambool but was tracking well into that contest. He's in the premier stable and his provincial and metro form is good enough. Deserves another chance. BROOKLYN BABY (14) was quickly back on track leading and winning a 62 at Kyneton. The 2kg claim is handy and she's sure to give a big sight. DRONE ATTACK (3) just missed at Pakenham before the spell spiking his figures. Has placed in two recent Cranbourne jumpouts and looks ready to go. An outside gate dampens expectations to some extent. HELLBERG (7) is going well enough to consider. He positions forward and gives himself every chance.
